ref-for-dom-idbcursor-advance①.name: advance
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-advance①.summary: The advance() method of the IDBCursor interface sets the number of times a cursor should move its position forward.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-advance①.title: IDBCursor: advance() method

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-continue①.name: continue
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-continue①.summary: The continue() method of the IDBCursor interface advances the cursor to the next position along its direction, to the item whose key matches the optional key parameter. If no key is specified, the cursor advances to the immediate next position, based on its direction.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-continue①.title: IDBCursor: continue() method

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-continueprimarykey.name: continuePrimaryKey
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-continueprimarykey.summary: The continuePrimaryKey() method of the IDBCursor interface advances the cursor to the item whose key matches the key parameter as well as whose primary key matches the primary key parameter.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-continueprimarykey.title: IDBCursor: continuePrimaryKey() method

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-delete①.name: delete
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-delete①.summary: The delete() method of the IDBCursor interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, deletes the record at the cursor's position, without changing the cursor's position. Once the record is deleted, the cursor's value is set to null.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-delete①.title: IDBCursor: delete() method

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-direction①.name: direction
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-direction①.summary: The direction read-only property of the IDBCursor interface is a string that returns the direction of traversal of the cursor (set using IDBObjectStore.openCursor for example). See the Values section below for possible values.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-direction①.title: IDBCursor: direction property

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-key①.name: key
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-key①.summary: The key read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the key for the record at the cursor's position. If the cursor is outside its range, this is set to undefined. The cursor's key can be any data type.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-key①.title: IDBCursor: key property

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-primarykey①.name: primaryKey
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-primarykey①.summary: The primaryKey read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the cursor's current effective key. If the cursor is currently being iterated or has iterated outside its range, this is set to undefined. The cursor's primary key can be any data type.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-primarykey①.title: IDBCursor: primaryKey property

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-request①.name: request
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-request①.summary: The request read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the IDBRequest used to obtain the cursor.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-request①.title: IDBCursor: request property

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-source①.name: source
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-source①.summary: The source read-only property of the IDBCursor interface returns the IDBObjectStore or IDBIndex that the cursor is iterating over. This function never returns null or throws an exception, even if the cursor is currently being iterated, has iterated past its end, or its transaction is not active.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-source①.title: IDBCursor: source property

ref-for-dom-idbcursor-update①.name: update
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-update①.summary: The update() method of the IDBCursor interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, updates the value at the current position of the cursor in the object store. If the cursor points to a record that has just been deleted, a new record is created.
ref-for-dom-idbcursor-update①.title: IDBCursor: update() method

cursor-interface.name: IDBCursor
cursor-interface.summary: The IDBCursor interface of the IndexedDB API represents a cursor for traversing or iterating over multiple records in a database.
cursor-interface.title: IDBCursor

ref-for-dom-idbcursorwithvalue-value①.name: value
ref-for-dom-idbcursorwithvalue-value①.summary: The value read-only property of the IDBCursorWithValue interface returns the value of the current cursor, whatever that is.
ref-for-dom-idbcursorwithvalue-value①.title: IDBCursorWithValue: value property

ref-for-idbcursorwithvalue②.name: IDBCursorWithValue
ref-for-idbcursorwithvalue②.summary: The IDBCursorWithValue interface of the IndexedDB API represents a cursor for traversing or iterating over multiple records in a database. It is the same as the IDBCursor, except that it includes the value property.
ref-for-idbcursorwithvalue②.title: IDBCursorWithValue

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-close②.name: close
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-close②.summary: The close() method of the IDBDatabase interface returns immediately and closes the connection in a separate thread.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-close②.title: IDBDatabase: close() method

closing-connection.name: close_event
closing-connection.summary: The close event is fired on IDBDatabase when the database connection is unexpectedly closed. This could happen, for example, if the underlying storage is removed or if the user clears the database in the browser's history preferences.
closing-connection.title: IDBDatabase: close event

dom-idbdatabase-onclose.name: close_event
dom-idbdatabase-onclose.summary: The close event is fired on IDBDatabase when the database connection is unexpectedly closed. This could happen, for example, if the underlying storage is removed or if the user clears the database in the browser's history preferences.
dom-idbdatabase-onclose.title: IDBDatabase: close event

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-createobjectstor.name: createObjectStore
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-createobjectstor.summary: The createObjectStore() method of the IDBDatabase interface creates and returns a new IDBObjectStore.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-createobjectstor.title: IDBDatabase: createObjectStore() method

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-deleteobjectstor.name: deleteObjectStore
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-deleteobjectstor.summary: The deleteObjectStore() method of the IDBDatabase interface destroys the object store with the given name in the connected database, along with any indexes that reference it.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-deleteobjectstor.title: IDBDatabase: deleteObjectStore() method

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-name①.name: name
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-name①.summary: The name read-only property of the IDBDatabase interface is a string that contains the name of the connected database.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-name①.title: IDBDatabase: name property

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.name: objectStoreNames
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.summary: The objectStoreNames read-only property of the IDBDatabase interface is a DOMStringList containing a list of the names of the object stores currently in the connected database.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-objectstorenames.title: IDBDatabase: objectStoreNames property

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-transaction③.name: transaction
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-transaction③.summary: The transaction method of the IDBDatabase interface immediately returns a transaction object (IDBTransaction) containing the IDBTransaction.objectStore method, which you can use to access your object store.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-transaction③.title: IDBDatabase: transaction() method

ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-version①.name: version
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-version①.summary: The version property of the IDBDatabase interface is a 64-bit integer that contains the version of the connected database. When a database is first created, this attribute is an empty string.
ref-for-dom-idbdatabase-version①.title: IDBDatabase: version property

eventdef-idbdatabase-versionchange.name: versionchange_event
eventdef-idbdatabase-versionchange.summary: The versionchange event is fired when a database structure change (upgradeneeded event send on an IDBOpenDBRequest or IDBFactory.deleteDatabase) was requested elsewhere (most probably in another window/tab on the same computer).
eventdef-idbdatabase-versionchange.title: IDBDatabase: versionchange event

dom-idbdatabase-onversionchange.name: versionchange_event
dom-idbdatabase-onversionchange.summary: The versionchange event is fired when a database structure change (upgradeneeded event send on an IDBOpenDBRequest or IDBFactory.deleteDatabase) was requested elsewhere (most probably in another window/tab on the same computer).
dom-idbdatabase-onversionchange.title: IDBDatabase: versionchange event

database-interface.name: IDBDatabase
database-interface.summary: The IDBDatabase interface of the IndexedDB API provides a connection to a database; you can use an IDBDatabase object to open a transaction on your database then create, manipulate, and delete objects (data) in that database. The interface provides the only way to get and manage versions of the database.
database-interface.title: IDBDatabase

ref-for-dom-idbfactory-cmp①.name: cmp
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-cmp①.summary: The cmp() method of the IDBFactory interface compares two values as keys to determine equality and ordering for IndexedDB operations, such as storing and iterating.
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-cmp①.title: IDBFactory: cmp() method

ref-for-dom-idbfactory-databases①.name: databases
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-databases①.summary: The databases method of the IDBFactory interface returns a list representing all the available databases, including their names and versions.
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-databases①.title: IDBFactory: databases() method

ref-for-dom-idbfactory-deletedatabase①.name: deleteDatabase
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-deletedatabase①.summary: The deleteDatabase() method of the IDBFactory interface requests the deletion of a database. The method returns an IDBOpenDBRequest object immediately, and performs the deletion operation asynchronously.
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-deletedatabase①.title: IDBFactory: deleteDatabase() method

ref-for-dom-idbfactory-open②.name: open
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-open②.summary: The open() method of the IDBFactory interface requests opening a connection to a database.
ref-for-dom-idbfactory-open②.title: IDBFactory: open() method

factory-interface.name: IDBFactory
factory-interface.summary: The IDBFactory interface of the IndexedDB API lets applications asynchronously access the indexed databases. The object that implements the interface is window.indexedDB. You open — that is, create and access — and delete a database with this object, and not directly with IDBFactory.
factory-interface.title: IDBFactory

ref-for-dom-idbindex-count①.name: count
ref-for-dom-idbindex-count①.summary: The count() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and in a separate thread, returns the number of records within a key range.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-count①.title: IDBIndex: count() method

ref-for-dom-idbindex-get①.name: get
ref-for-dom-idbindex-get①.summary: The get() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, finds either the value in the referenced object store that corresponds to the given key or the first corresponding value, if key is set to an IDBKeyRange.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-get①.title: IDBIndex: get() method

ref-for-dom-idbindex-getall①.name: getAll
ref-for-dom-idbindex-getall①.summary: The getAll() method of the IDBIndex interface retrieves all objects that are inside the index.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-getall①.title: IDBIndex: getAll() method

ref-for-dom-idbindex-getallkeys①.name: getAllKeys
ref-for-dom-idbindex-getallkeys①.summary: The getAllKeys() method of the IDBIndex interface asynchronously retrieves the primary keys of all objects inside the index, setting them as the result of the request object.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-getallkeys①.title: IDBIndex: getAllKeys() method

ref-for-dom-idbindex-getkey①.name: getKey
ref-for-dom-idbindex-getkey①.summary: The getKey() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, finds either the primary key that corresponds to the given key in this index or the first corresponding primary key, if key is set to an IDBKeyRange.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-getkey①.title: IDBIndex: getKey() method

dom-idbindex-keypath.name: keyPath
dom-idbindex-keypath.summary: The keyPath property of the IDBIndex interface returns the key path of the current index. If null, this index is not auto-populated.
dom-idbindex-keypath.title: IDBIndex: keyPath property

dom-idbindex-multientry.name: multiEntry
dom-idbindex-multientry.summary: The multiEntry read-only property of the IDBIndex interface returns a boolean value that affects how the index behaves when the result of evaluating the index's key path yields an array.
dom-idbindex-multientry.title: IDBIndex: multiEntry property

ref-for-dom-idbindex-name①.name: name
ref-for-dom-idbindex-name①.summary: The name property of the IDBIndex interface contains a string which names the index.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-name①.title: IDBIndex: name property

ref-for-dom-idbindex-objectstore①.name: objectStore
ref-for-dom-idbindex-objectstore①.summary: The objectStore property of the IDBIndex interface returns the name of the object store referenced by the current index.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-objectstore①.title: IDBIndex: objectStore property

ref-for-dom-idbindex-opencursor②.name: openCursor
ref-for-dom-idbindex-opencursor②.summary: The openCursor() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, creates a cursor over the specified key range.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-opencursor②.title: IDBIndex: openCursor() method

ref-for-dom-idbindex-openkeycursor①.name: openKeyCursor
ref-for-dom-idbindex-openkeycursor①.summary: The openKeyCursor() method of the IDBIndex interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, creates a cursor over the specified key range, as arranged by this index.
ref-for-dom-idbindex-openkeycursor①.title: IDBIndex: openKeyCursor() method

dom-idbindex-unique.name: unique
dom-idbindex-unique.summary: The unique read-only property returns a boolean that states whether the index allows duplicate keys.
dom-idbindex-unique.title: IDBIndex: unique property

index-interface.name: IDBIndex
index-interface.summary: IDBIndex interface of the IndexedDB API provides asynchronous access to an index in a database. An index is a kind of object store for looking up records in another object store, called the referenced object store. You use this interface to retrieve data.
index-interface.title: IDBIndex

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-bound①.name: bound_static
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-bound①.summary: The bound() static method of the IDBKeyRange interface creates a new key range with the specified upper and lower bounds. The bounds can be open (that is, the bounds exclude the endpoint values) or closed (that is, the bounds include the endpoint values). By default, the bounds are closed.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-bound①.title: IDBKeyRange: bound() static method

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-includes①.name: includes
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-includes①.summary: The includes() method of the IDBKeyRange interface returns a boolean indicating whether a specified key is inside the key range.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-includes①.title: IDBKeyRange: includes() method

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-lower①.name: lower
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-lower①.summary: The lower read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns the lower bound of the key range.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-lower①.title: IDBKeyRange: lower property

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-lowerbound①.name: lowerBound_static
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-lowerbound①.summary: The lowerBound() static method of the IDBKeyRange interface creates a new key range with only a lower bound. By default, it includes the lower endpoint value and is closed.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-lowerbound①.title: IDBKeyRange: lowerBound() static method

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-loweropen①.name: lowerOpen
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-loweropen①.summary: The lowerOpen read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns a boolean indicating whether the lower-bound value is included in the key range.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-loweropen①.title: IDBKeyRange: lowerOpen property

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-only①.name: only_static
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-only①.summary: The only() static method of the IDBKeyRange interface creates a new key range containing a single value.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-only①.title: IDBKeyRange: only() static method

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upper①.name: upper
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upper①.summary: The upper read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns the upper bound of the key range.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upper①.title: IDBKeyRange: upper property

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upperbound①.name: upperBound_static
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upperbound①.summary: The upperBound() static method of the IDBKeyRange interface creates a new upper-bound key range. By default, it includes the upper endpoint value and is closed.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upperbound①.title: IDBKeyRange: upperBound() static method

ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upperopen①.name: upperOpen
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upperopen①.summary: The upperOpen read-only property of the IDBKeyRange interface returns a boolean indicating whether the upper-bound value is included in the key range.
ref-for-dom-idbkeyrange-upperopen①.title: IDBKeyRange: upperOpen property

keyrange.name: IDBKeyRange
keyrange.summary: The IDBKeyRange interface of the IndexedDB API represents a continuous interval over some data type that is used for keys. Records can be retrieved from IDBObjectStore and IDBIndex objects using keys or a range of keys. You can limit the range using lower and upper bounds. For example, you can iterate over all values of a key in the value range A–Z.
keyrange.title: IDBKeyRange

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-add①.name: add
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-add①.summary: The add() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, creates a structured clone of the value, and stores the cloned value in the object store. This is for adding new records to an object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-add①.title: IDBObjectStore: add() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-autoincrement.name: autoIncrement
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-autoincrement.summary: The autoIncrement read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns the value of the auto increment flag for this object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-autoincrement.title: IDBObjectStore: autoIncrement property

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-clear③.name: clear
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-clear③.summary: The clear() method of the IDBObjectStore interface creates and immediately returns an IDBRequest object, and clears this object store in a separate thread. This is for deleting all the current data out of an object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-clear③.title: IDBObjectStore: clear() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-count①.name: count
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-count①.summary: The count() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns the total number of records that match the provided key or IDBKeyRange. If no arguments are provided, it returns the total number of records in the store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-count①.title: IDBObjectStore: count() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-createindex①.name: createIndex
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-createindex①.summary: The createIndex() method of the IDBObjectStore interface creates and returns a new IDBIndex object in the connected database. It creates a new field/column defining a new data point for each database record to contain.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-createindex①.title: IDBObjectStore: createIndex() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-delete①.name: delete
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-delete①.summary: The delete() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, deletes the specified record or records.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-delete①.title: IDBObjectStore: delete() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-deleteindex①.name: deleteIndex
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-deleteindex①.summary: The deleteIndex() method of the IDBObjectStore interface destroys the index with the specified name in the connected database, used during a version upgrade.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-deleteindex①.title: IDBObjectStore: deleteIndex() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-get①.name: get
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-get①.summary: The get() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns the object selected by the specified key. This is for retrieving specific records from an object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-get①.title: IDBObjectStore: get() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getall①.name: getAll
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getall①.summary: The getAll() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object containing all objects in the object store matching the specified parameter or all objects in the store if no parameters are given.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getall①.title: IDBObjectStore: getAll() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getallkeys①.name: getAllKeys
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getallkeys①.summary: The getAllKeys() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object retrieves record keys for all objects in the object store matching the specified parameter or all objects in the store if no parameters are given.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getallkeys①.title: IDBObjectStore: getAllKeys() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getkey①.name: getKey
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getkey①.summary: The getKey() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns the key selected by the specified query. This is for retrieving specific records from an object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-getkey①.title: IDBObjectStore: getKey() method

dom-idbobjectstore-index.name: index
dom-idbobjectstore-index.summary: The index() method of the IDBObjectStore interface opens a named index in the current object store, after which it can be used to, for example, return a series of records sorted by that index using a cursor.
dom-idbobjectstore-index.title: IDBObjectStore: index() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-indexnames①.name: indexNames
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-indexnames①.summary: The indexNames read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns a list of the names of indexes on objects in this object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-indexnames①.title: IDBObjectStore: indexNames property

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-keypath①.name: keyPath
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-keypath①.summary: The keyPath read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns the key path of this object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-keypath①.title: IDBObjectStore: keyPath property

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-name①.name: name
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-name①.summary: The name property of the IDBObjectStore interface indicates the name of this object store.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-name①.title: IDBObjectStore: name property

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-opencursor②.name: openCursor
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-opencursor②.summary: The openCursor() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object, and, in a separate thread, returns a new IDBCursorWithValue object. Used for iterating through an object store with a cursor.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-opencursor②.title: IDBObjectStore: openCursor() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-openkeycursor.name: openKeyCursor
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-openkeycursor.summary: The openKeyCursor() method of the IDBObjectStore interface returns an IDBRequest object whose result will be set to an IDBCursor that can be used to iterate through matching results. Used for iterating through the keys of an object store with a cursor.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-openkeycursor.title: IDBObjectStore: openKeyCursor() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-put①.name: put
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-put①.summary: The put() method of the IDBObjectStore interface updates a given record in a database, or inserts a new record if the given item does not already exist.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-put①.title: IDBObjectStore: put() method

ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-transaction①.name: transaction
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-transaction①.summary: The transaction read-only property of the IDBObjectStore interface returns the transaction object to which this object store belongs.
ref-for-dom-idbobjectstore-transaction①.title: IDBObjectStore: transaction property

object-store-interface.name: IDBObjectStore
object-store-interface.summary: The IDBObjectStore interface of the IndexedDB API represents an object store in a database. Records within an object store are sorted according to their keys. This sorting enables fast insertion, look-up, and ordered retrieval.
object-store-interface.title: IDBObjectStore

eventdef-idbopendbrequest-blocked.name: blocked_event
eventdef-idbopendbrequest-blocked.summary: The blocked handler is executed when an open connection to a database is blocking a versionchange transaction on the same database.
eventdef-idbopendbrequest-blocked.title: IDBOpenDBRequest: blocked event

eventdef-idbopendbrequest-upgradeneeded.name: upgradeneeded_event
eventdef-idbopendbrequest-upgradeneeded.summary: The upgradeneeded event is fired when an attempt was made to open a database with a version number higher than its current version.
eventdef-idbopendbrequest-upgradeneeded.title: IDBOpenDBRequest: upgradeneeded event

idbopendbrequest.name: IDBOpenDBRequest
idbopendbrequest.summary: The IDBOpenDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to the results of requests to open or delete databases (performed using IDBFactory.open and IDBFactory.deleteDatabase), using specific event handler attributes.
idbopendbrequest.title: IDBOpenDBRequest

ref-for-dom-idbrequest-error①.name: error
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-error①.summary: The error read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the error in the event of an unsuccessful request.
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-error①.title: IDBRequest: error property

eventdef-idbrequest-error.name: error_event
eventdef-idbrequest-error.summary: The error handler is executed when an error caused a request to fail.
eventdef-idbrequest-error.title: IDBRequest: error event

eventdef-idbrequest-error.name: error_event
eventdef-idbrequest-error.summary: The error event is fired on IDBTransaction when a request returns an error and the event bubbles up to the transaction object.
eventdef-idbrequest-error.title: IDBTransaction: error event

ref-for-dom-idbrequest-readystate①.name: readyState
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-readystate①.summary: The readyState read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the state of the request.
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-readystate①.title: IDBRequest: readyState property

ref-for-dom-idbrequest-result①.name: result
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-result①.summary: The result read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the result of the request. If the request is not completed, the result is not available and an InvalidStateError exception is thrown.
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-result①.title: IDBRequest: result property

ref-for-dom-idbrequest-source①.name: source
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-source①.summary: The source read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the source of the request, such as an Index or an object store. If no source exists (such as when calling IDBFactory.open), it returns null.
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-source①.title: IDBRequest: source property

eventdef-idbrequest-success.name: success_event
eventdef-idbrequest-success.summary: The success event is fired when an IDBRequest succeeds.
eventdef-idbrequest-success.title: IDBRequest: success event

ref-for-dom-idbrequest-transaction①.name: transaction
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-transaction①.summary: The transaction read-only property of the IDBRequest interface returns the transaction for the request, that is, the transaction the request is being made inside.
ref-for-dom-idbrequest-transaction①.title: IDBRequest: transaction property

request-api.name: IDBRequest
request-api.summary: The IDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to results of asynchronous requests to databases and database objects using event handler attributes. Each reading and writing operation on a database is done using a request.
request-api.title: IDBRequest

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-abort②.name: abort
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-abort②.summary: The abort() method of the IDBTransaction interface rolls back all the changes to objects in the database associated with this transaction.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-abort②.title: IDBTransaction: abort() method

eventdef-idbtransaction-abort.name: abort_event
eventdef-idbtransaction-abort.summary: The abort event is fired when an IndexedDB transaction is aborted.
eventdef-idbtransaction-abort.title: IDBTransaction: abort event

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-commit②.name: commit
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-commit②.summary: The commit() method of the IDBTransaction interface commits the transaction if it is called on an active transaction.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-commit②.title: IDBTransaction: commit() method

eventdef-idbtransaction-complete.name: complete_event
eventdef-idbtransaction-complete.summary: The complete event of the IndexedDB API is fired when the transaction successfully completed.
eventdef-idbtransaction-complete.title: IDBTransaction: complete event

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-db①.name: db
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-db①.summary: The db read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns the database connection with which this transaction is associated.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-db①.title: IDBTransaction: db property

dom-idbtransaction-durability.name: durability
dom-idbtransaction-durability.summary: The durability read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns the durability hint the transaction was created with. This is a hint to the user agent of whether to prioritize performance or durability when committing the transaction.
dom-idbtransaction-durability.title: IDBTransaction: durability property

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-error①.name: error
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-error①.summary: The IDBTransaction.error property of the IDBTransaction interface returns the type of error when there is an unsuccessful transaction.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-error①.title: IDBTransaction: error property

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-mode①.name: mode
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-mode①.summary: The mode read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns the current mode for accessing the data in the object stores in the scope of the transaction (i.e. is the mode to be read-only, or do you want to write to the object stores?) The default value is readonly.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-mode①.title: IDBTransaction: mode property

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-objectstore①.name: objectStore
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-objectstore①.summary: The objectStore() method of the IDBTransaction interface returns an object store that has already been added to the scope of this transaction.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-objectstore①.title: IDBTransaction: objectStore() method

ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-objectstorena.name: objectStoreNames
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-objectstorena.summary: The objectStoreNames read-only property of the IDBTransaction interface returns a DOMStringList of names of IDBObjectStore objects.
ref-for-dom-idbtransaction-objectstorena.title: IDBTransaction: objectStoreNames property

transaction.name: IDBTransaction
transaction.summary: The IDBTransaction interface of the IndexedDB API provides a static, asynchronous transaction on a database using event handler attributes. All reading and writing of data is done within transactions. You use IDBDatabase to start transactions, IDBTransaction to set the mode of the transaction (e.g. is it readonly or readwrite), and you access an IDBObjectStore to make a request. You can also use an IDBTransaction object to abort transactions.
transaction.title: IDBTransaction

dom-idbversionchangeevent-idbversionchan.name: IDBVersionChangeEvent
dom-idbversionchangeevent-idbversionchan.summary: The IDBVersionChangeEvent() constructor creates a new IDBVersionChangeEvent object, which is used to represent when a version of the database has changed, as a result of the onupgradeneeded event handler.
dom-idbversionchangeevent-idbversionchan.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent: IDBVersionChangeEvent() constructor

dom-idbversionchangeevent-newversion.name: newVersion
dom-idbversionchangeevent-newversion.summary: The newVersion read-only property of the IDBVersionChangeEvent interface returns the new version number of the database.
dom-idbversionchangeevent-newversion.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent: newVersion property

dom-idbversionchangeevent-oldversion.name: oldVersion
dom-idbversionchangeevent-oldversion.summary: The oldVersion read-only property of the IDBVersionChangeEvent interface returns the old version number of the database.
dom-idbversionchangeevent-oldversion.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent: oldVersion property

events.name: IDBVersionChangeEvent
events.summary: The IDBVersionChangeEvent interface of the IndexedDB API indicates that the version of the database has changed, as the result of an onupgradeneeded event handler function.
events.title: IDBVersionChangeEvent

dom-windoworworkerglobalscope-indexeddb.name: indexedDB
dom-windoworworkerglobalscope-indexeddb.summary: The global indexedDB read-only property provides a mechanism for applications to asynchronously access the capabilities of indexed databases.
dom-windoworworkerglobalscope-indexeddb.title: indexedDB global property
